    • parseFlightData

      public static ScoreCalculation parseFlightData(String filePath, String name)
      Parses out the phases of the flight and creates a ScoreCalculations object. Data entries prior to the initial approach fix (JIPOX) are discarded. Data entries between JIPOX and before final approach fix are included in the stepdown phase. Data entries at or after the final approach fix and above the minimum approach altitude are included in the final approach phase. Data entries at or below the minimum approach altitude and with non-positive ground roll value are included in the Roundout phase. Data entries with positive ground roll values are included in the landing phase. These phases/categories do not overlap.
      Parameters:
      filePath - path to flight data csv file.
      name - Participant name or identifier.
      Returns:
      pilot success score as a ScoreCalculation object.
